{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"sharpcut-actual-larva","description":"## Why\nTwo known tickets (115b, 8c4f) burned close-gate cycles because operational ACs (evidence outside the codebase) were not tagged [operator-attested] until the close gate forced it - a cheap deterministic lint at plan time removes that whole round-trip. AQUSA-grade rule-based checks are the proven high-recall/cheap tier for this defect shape.\n\n## What\nA P6-adjacent DET lint (pass-1 deterministic floor family, advisory posture): a lexicon of operational-evidence markers (deploy/prod/console/live run/vote/operator drill/...) flags AC checklist items whose evidence inherently lives outside the codebase but lack the [operator-attested] tag. Self-gated by its own eval BEFORE landing: run the lexicon over the full historical AC corpus (from E1's outcome corpus tickets); gate row = >=70% sampled precision, <=5% overall flag rate, and both known cases (115b, 8c4f) fire. Incorporated directly into the packaged DET floor on pass (advisory; DET criteria are prompt-less per ADR 0016).\n\n## Scope\n- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py + criteria_routing.json (new DET entry, advisory).\n- docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/ (lexicon eval writeup + runs/ artifact).\n- Unit tests: known-case fixtures (115b/8c4f AC texts) + negative controls.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The lexicon eval over the full historical AC corpus is committed BEFORE the lint lands, recording >=70% sampled precision (>=50-item sample) and <=5% overall flag rate; a failing eval defers the story with the result recorded.\n- [ ] Both known cases fire: the 115b and 8c4f AC texts are flagged, pinned as unit-test fixtures.\n- [ ] The lint ships advisory in the packaged registry (no config flag), with rubric-free DET routing per ADR 0016, and docs/plan-review-gate.md documents it.","id":"b080-fa0b-b1ce-4fad","parent_id":"6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"R2: operator-attested evidence-kind DET lint (P6 family, advisory)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784143868974779001,"uuid":"5e988a34-563b-47f5-a2ea-76e333a3a093"}